Paratypes
. LBP 7066, 10, 3 C&S, 35.2–44.4 mm SL;
MZUSP 125292 , 2 , 41.0– 41.2 mm SL
;
ZUEC 17134 , 2 , 35.3–39.3 mm SL, same data as holotype
.

Mouth terminal. Premaxillary teeth arranged in two rows; outer row with 4*(13) or 5(2) tricuspid teeth, median cusp more pronounced than remaining cusps. Inner row with 5 pentacuspid teeth, median cusp more pronounced than remaining cusps. Maxillar with 2*(10) or 3(5) teeth with one to five cusps. Dentary with 4 large pentacuspid teeth, followed by a series of very small teeth with one to three cusps (
Fig. 2
).
